title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points.
Overall Youth unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Youth unemployment rate is roughly constant from 1999 to 2001, rapidly increasing from 2001 to 2005, slightly decreasing from 2005 to 2007, roughly constant from 2007 to 2011, roughly increasing from 2011 to 2013, slightly decreasing from 2013 to 2016, and lastly roughly constant from 2016 to 2019.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 2015 and 2016.
Max Youth unemployment rate about 33.82 was recorded at Year 2006
Min Youth unemployment rate about 23.18 was recorded at Year 1999
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Youth unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 5 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely increasing which exists from 1999 to 2006.
Correspondingly, the next significant trend is slightly increasing which exists from 2012 to 2016.
Additionally, the next significant trend is moderately increasing which exists from 2016 to 2019.
Also, the next significant trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2009 to 2012.
Contrarily, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2006 to 2009.
